Journalist Nicky Taylor travels to Amsterdam to investigate the growing
  debate about the legal classification of cannabis. While there she helps
  out in a coffee shop that sells the drug, and discovers first hand what
  the effects of cannabis are on everyday life. Back in the UK Nicky finds
  out about the genetically modified cannabis skunk, cheap and increasingly
  sold on the streets. The programme asks whether the drug can make you mad,
  if it is worse than alcohol and if it is stronger than it used to be.
  Nicky takes part in a month-long medical trial to find out.
